<Window x:Class="EspOledTemp.aboutWindow"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:EspOledTemp"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="About" Height="250" Width="320"
        Background="LightBlue"
        MouseDown="aboutClicked"
        >
        
        <Grid Margin="10,10,10,10">
        
        <Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
            <ColumnDefinition Width="175*"/>
        </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
        <Grid.RowDefinitions>
            <RowDefinition Height="55" />
            <RowDefinition Height="55" />
        </Grid.RowDefinitions>
        
        <TextBlock x:Name="aboutTxt" 
            TextWrapping="WrapWithOverflow"
            Padding ="5"
            Margin="0,0,-56,-44"
            Width="298"
            HorizontalAlignment="Left"
            Grid.Row="0"
            >
           The base for this project is a NodeMCU, a Soc based on ESP8266. It has a sensor for temperature and humidity connected, a HTU21D module. It also have an OLED connected for showing measured values, these values are also sent via Mqtt to a Mqtt-broker. The values are also presented via a dynamic webpage where you can see the values in near realtime.
            This program is a Windows app that receives the Mqtt-values and display them in a window.
            More info at https://github.com/bphermansson/EspOledTemp and https://github.com/bphermansson/EspOledTemp_Csharp.
        </TextBlock>
        <RichTextBox IsReadOnly="True" IsDocumentEnabled="True"
                        Grid.Row="1"
         >
            <FlowDocument>
                <Paragraph>
                    Please enter your details for login: questions follow the link
                    <Hyperlink NavigateUri='https:www.paheco.nu' >
                        Reset Password
                    </Hyperlink>
                    RequestNavigate="Hyperlink_RequestNavigateAbout">

                </Paragraph>
            </FlowDocument>
        </RichTextBox>
    </Grid>
</Window>
